\begin_layout Itemize
After auctioning the private companies, the game consists of an alternating
 series of Stock Rounds and sets of one to four Operating Rounds
\noun on
.
 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The round marker is used to track the game's progress through the rounds.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In Stock Rounds, players may buy and sell shares of public companies, taking
 and losing control of public companies, merging public companies into systems
 and starting new public companies (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Stock-Rounds"

\end_inset

 & 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Systems"

\end_inset

).
 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
After each Stock Round ends, the player order for the next Stock Round is
 determined by the order in which the players cease acting (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Stock-Round-overview"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The number of Operating Rounds per set after a Stock Round
\noun on
 
\noun default
is determined by the current game phase at the end of the Stock Round (see
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
