\begin_layout Itemize
The player that holds the most shares of a public company (largest total
 percentage) is the director of the public company, has the 20% director's
 share of the public company and controls all of that company's operations
 (if it has floated, see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Starting-or-floating"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If a player buys shares such that they own a larger percentage of the public
 company than the current director:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
They become the new company director by exchanging company certificates
 totaling 20% of the public company for the 20% director's certificate of
 the public company and taking control of the public company charter and
 its assets.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The director's share can never be sold, only transferred to another player.
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Once a public company has floated, there is always a player that owns the
 20% director's certificate and is the director of the public company.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In order to transfer director control of a public company via share sales:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The director's share must be exchanged for certificates of the player with
 the most shares of the public company after the sale, assigning control
 of the public company and its charter and assets to that player.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The previous director must sell sufficient shares of the public company
 such that they own fewer shares of the public company than the new director
 after the sale.
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In the case of a tie among other players for the most shares after the sale,
 the next tied player in player number card order from the current director
 becomes the new director and receives the director's certificate in exchange.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
