\begin_layout Subsubsection
Track placement overview 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "par:track-placement-Overview"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Only yellow track tiles are available at the beginning of the game.
 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Later in the game green and brown track tiles become available (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

 & 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Upgrading-track"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Track tiles can be placed on the towns, cities and rural hexagons of the
 map and cannot be placed on red off-board hexagons, or gray pre-built hexagons
 (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Map-Explanation"

\end_inset

).
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Once a track tile of a given type is placed in a hexagon:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Terrain costs for the hexagon are not paid again in future tile upgrades.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
After placing or upgrading a track tile the placing public company must
 be able to trace a continuous line of track from one of its station markers
 to a line of track on the placed track tile without:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Passing through a city all of whose station-marker spaces are filled with
 other public company's station markers.
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Passing through the Virginia Coalfields (K12) if the public company doesn't
 already own a coal token.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Crossing any hexagon-edge twice.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Track tiles must not be placed such that a line of track:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Already present is not preserved by the new track tile.
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Only the connectivity is important, not the exact shape of the line of track.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Runs off the edge of the map (no further hexagons).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Runs to the edge of a gray pre-built hexagon which doesn't have pre-printed
 track running to it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Runs to the edge of a red off-board hexagon which doesn't have a black triangle/
arrow to indicate a continuation for the track.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Runs into a blue barrier between hexagons (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Map-Explanation"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
A public company placing a track tile on a river ($80) or mountain ($120)
 hexagon which has not previously contained a track tile must pay the terrain
 cost from its treasury to the bank before placing the tile (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Map-Explanation"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Virginia Coalfields 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A public company that does not own a coal token (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Game-end-criteria"

\end_inset

):
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Cannot place track that can't trace a route to one of the public company's
 station markers without passing through the Virginia Coalfields (K12).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Cannot include the Virginia Coalfields on a train's route (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Trains-and-Running-Trains"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Paragraph
Virginia Coalfields Tunnel
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Only a #4 yellow town tile may be placed on the Virginia Coalfields Tunnel
 (K14).
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The tile must be placed matching the dotted track pre-drawn on the hexagon.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
There is a terrain cost of $120 (mountain).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The building public company is automatically awarded the coal token placed
 there during setup (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Game-Setup"

\end_inset

).
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If the public company already has a coal token:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
It must return one of them to the supply on the Virgina Coalfields (K12).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection
Upgrading track
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:Upgrading-track"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Starting in green phase: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Public companies may upgrade yellow track tiles and yellow map hexagons
 to green track tiles (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Starting in brown phase:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Public companies may also upgrade green track tiles to brown track tiles
 (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
When upgrading a track tile:
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The type of the track tile cannot be changed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Connections of pairs of hexagon edges by lines of track must be preserved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Connections of city circles to hexagon edges by lines of track must be preserved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A public company cannot upgrade a track tile it has upgraded or placed in
 that same Operating Round.6
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The upgraded track tile is returned to the supply for future use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If a track tile on a river or hill area is upgraded, the terrain cost is
 not paid again (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Map-Explanation"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Station markers are moved to their corresponding locations on the new tile
 when upgrading a track tile or hexagon
\end_layout

